Voiceover (VO) Script
 
[0:00 - 0:15]
Hook & The Problem
A beautiful morning shot of a Texas suburban neighborhood or local trail. Suddenly, a smartphone screen pops up showing a notification blur. Cut to a quick, slightly tense shot of a rustle in the bushes, or a glimpse of a copperhead snake near a walking path.
"Texas is famous for its wide-open spaces, beautiful trails, and... some incredibly diverse wildlife. But when you’re out for a morning jog or your kids are playing in the yard, a surprise encounter can change everything in seconds."
[0:15 - 0:35]
Introducing TexaFauna
Smooth transition to a smartphone displaying the TexaFauna logo. Animated hands tap through the app, showing a clean, user-friendly interface.

A user snaps a quick photo of a bobcat from a safe distance and uploads it. The app’s AI interface instantly highlights the animal, identifies it, and flashes a color-coded status bar: [Danger Level: High].
"Meet TexaFauna—the community-driven wildlife monitoring app built specifically for Texans to keep our neighborhoods informed and safe.

Spot something on your path? Just snap a photo or type a quick description. TexaFauna’s AI-powered identification instantly logs the species, tags the exact GPS coordinates, and maps out a predicted movement radius in real time."
[0:35 - 0:55]
Core Features & Real-Time Safety
Screen shifts to the Live Tracking Map. Little animal icons populate the screen. A specific icon for a copperhead shows a radius around it. The map seamlessly pulls in official data, showing a "Verified City of Frisco Wildlife Data" tag.

The phone screen mimics a lock screen, and a push notification slides down: “TexaFauna Alert: Critical Sighting (Venomous Snake) within 0.5 miles of your location.”
"Track animal activity instantly. Our live map combines community reports with official city data, giving you the most accurate view of your surroundings. And if you lose cell service on the trail? No worries—offline caching keeps recent reports right on your screen.

Set your personal safety perimeter. With real-time danger alerts tailored to your customizable radius, you’ll get instant notifications—and optional email alerts—the second a critical threat is reported nearby."
[0:55 - 1:15]
Education, Community, & CTA
Fast cuts of the remaining features:
Flipping to the Safety Section, showing step-by-step guidance on what to do if you encounter a predator, followed by clear first-aid instructions.
A quick scroll through the Sighting History page showing a clean 6-month bar chart trend.
The Community Gallery and the Monthly Contributor Leaderboard showing local users earning points.
A family walking their dog safely down a trail, looking relaxed. The final frame features the TexaFauna app mockup next to App Store and Google Play badges.

Text on Screen: TexaFauna. Explore safely. Protect your community.
"TexaFauna is more than a map—it’s a safety toolkit. Access expert encounter guidance and instant first-aid instructions for Texas's native predators, venomous snakes, and spiders. Track six-month wildlife trends, share photos to the gallery, and climb the contributor leaderboard as you help protect your neighbors.

Knowledge is safety. Download TexaFauna today, stay aware, and keep Texas safe, one report at a time."


